</section>

<!-- BIO -->
<section class="bio-section">
  <div class="bio-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">About Scott</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">The American Who Keeps Coming Back</h2>
    <div class="bio-content">
      <p>Travel has always been my escape from the everyday &mdash; and honestly, I enjoy the <strong>planning</strong> almost as much as being there. Researching destinations, mapping train routes, finding that perfect trattoria tucked down a side street. My first trip to Italy changed everything &mdash; I stepped off the train in Rome and knew this country was going to become a major part of my life.</p>
      <p>Since that first visit, I've returned again and again &mdash; exploring Tuscany's hilltop towns, getting lost in Venice's labyrinth of canals, eating my way through Naples and Bologna, hiking the Cinque Terre trails, and discovering the quieter corners of Sicily, Puglia, and Umbria that most tourists never see.</p>
      <p><strong>I'm not a traditional travel blogger. I work in healthcare IT.</strong> But Italy keeps pulling me back, and I finally decided to put everything I've learned into something useful &mdash; a site with real knowledge, honest prices, video content from the places I've actually been, and an AI trip planner that builds itineraries from years of real experience.</p>
      <p>Discovering Italy is the resource I wished existed when I first started planning trips here. It just took this long to figure out how to build it.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CREDENTIALS -->
